Once all your mri data is bidsified, it's time to run fmriprep. 
It's better to run it on a cluster (you can run it locally, but this will take much longer)
A cluster that I like to use is the SCC. Fist you have to set up an SCC account, once you do that you're ready to get started!

First you have to upload all your bidsified data along with your fmriprep codes,and templates folder, unto the SCC
These are the paths to these:
  fmriprep codes: /Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/codes/codes/fmriprep_code
  templates:/Raid/Current/Miray/MRI/templates

To upload files to SCC, you have to open a new terminal (do not log into SCC!) and type command: 
scp -v -r /path/to/folder/you/wanna/move scc_username@local_computer_ip_address:/output/path/in/scc

Then, on the SCC create 2 new folders
mkdir work
mkdir temp

Once your BIDS_OUPUT folder is uploaded, you can run fmriprep
